%N A396601 Odd numbers k where sigma_4(k)/k is an integer.
%C A396601 Compared to A396599 (sigma_2(k)/k) and A396600 (sigma_3(k)/k), odd terms are rarer.
%H A396601 Alexander Violette, <a href="/A396601/b396601.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..47</a>
%H A396601 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Divisor_function">Divisor function</a>.
%e A396601 (1^4 + 41^4 + 137^4 + 5617^4)/5617 is an integer, making 5617 a term of this sequence.
%t A396601 Select[Range[1, 10^6, 2], Divisible[DivisorSigma[4, #], #] &] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 06 2026 *)
%o A396601 (PARI) isok(k) = (k%2) && (denominator(sigma(k,4)/k) == 1); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Jun 06 2026
